      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "*numbers, = map(int,input().split())\n\nbit_options = ['{:04b}'.format(x) for x in range(16)]\n\nif sum(numbers)==24:\n    answer = 'add'\nelse:\n    answer = 'not possible'\n    for bits in bit_options:\n        operators = bits.replace('0','-').replace('1','+')\n        calculation = 0\n        for operator,number in zip(operators,numbers):\n            exec(f'calculation{operator}={number}')\n        if calculation==24:\n            answer = 'add/subtract'\n            break\n\nprint(answer)",
      "statement": "With the <<24 game>>, you have to find a way to turn a given set of four numbers into 24 with different mathematical operators. For this clash, only the operators {{+}} (addition) and {{-}} (subtraction) are to be used.\n\nFor a given set of 4 numbers, you have to output:\n{{add}} if the 4 numbers can result in 24 by addition only (e.g. 6+6+6+6);\n{{add/subtract}} if the 4 numbers can result in 24 by addition and subtraction (e.g. 10+10+10-6) or subtraction only (e.g. 27-1-1-1); or\n{{not possible}} if it is not possible (e.g. 2,2,2,2, which can never result in 24 with addition and/or subtraction).",
